    new Double(100);
    int i = 100;
    new Double(i);
    Integer i1 = 100;
    new Double(i1);
    double d1 = (double) i;

There is a new [Decimal128 BSON data type][2] available since 3.4 version. 

The Java API can take `BigDecimal` or `long` value to construct the Decimal128 object. Please refer the above API documentation.

Refer this [blog][3] to understand why Decimal128 is needed?

[Floating point arithmetic accuracy problems][4]


